I'm wondering WHAT if any method they will employ to keep the ranks of Jedi from becoming ridiculously bloated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/02 12:41:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15969.topic&index=79>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/jarninface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  You are trying to strip Jedi down to be less powerful than they are meant to be in the name of balance, which would work but wouldn't accurately represent the Star Wars universe - which is sort of the POINT of having a Star Wars Massive Multiplayer Game.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
How powerful are Jedi supposed to be Grim? As powerful as wizards in EQ? I know you won't agree with that. I've been reading your posts for almost 2 years now.<br>
